parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Failure (Yamaha Raptor 660 and YZF R1)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, lock up, or slip, leading to accidents, injuries, or even death. This can occur suddenly, without warning, and may result in loss of control, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: causing the vehicle to lose power or momentum. The rider may experience a sudden loss of control
resulting in accidents or near-misses. Other symptoms include a loud pop or grinding noise

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the 2nd gear can cause the vehicle to slip or jump out of gear, leading to loss of control, accidents, or injuries. This can occur suddenly, without warning, and may result in loss of momentum or power.
symptoms: The 2nd gear slips or fails to engage
causing the vehicle to lose power or momentum. The rider may experience a sudden loss of control
resulting in accidents or near-misses. Other symptoms include a loud pop or grinding noise

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and starter can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or fail to start, leading to accidents, injuries, or strandings. This can occur suddenly, without warning, and may result in loss of control or momentum.
symptoms: The clutch and starter fail to engage
causing the vehicle to lose power or stall. The rider may experience difficulty starting the vehicle
or the vehicle may fail to start altogether. Other symptoms include a loud pop or grinding noise

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the lights to stay on even when the key is removed, and the engine can still crank but won't start unless the key is in the "on" position, which can lead to battery drain and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Lights stay on when the key is removed
engine cranks with the key removed but won't start

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The battery acid leak can cause corrosion of metal parts, including the rear shock absorber, swingarm, and chain, which can lead to accidents or leave the rider stranded.
symptoms: White spots or corrosion on the rear swingarm
battery acid leaking onto the rear swingarm

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The leakage of battery acid can cause corrosion to major suspension and drive components, leading to structural damage and potentially catastrophic failure, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: foreign material on the shock absorber and swing arm
signs of acid leakage around the battery.
